127  void SpellHit(Unit* pCaster, const SpellEntry* pSpell) override
128  {
129  if (pSpell->Id == SPELL_T_PHASE_MODULATOR && pCaster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
130  {
131  // we are nihil, so say before transform
132  if (m_creature->GetEntry() == NPC_NIHIL)
133  {
134  DoScriptText(SAY_NIHIL_INTERRUPT, m_creature);
135  m_creature->RemoveFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_SPAWNING);
136  m_bIsNihil = false;
137  }
138 
139  // choose a new entry
140  uint8 uiIndex = urand(0, MAX_ENTRIES - 1);
141 
142  // If we choose the same entry, try again
143  while (aNetherDrakeEntries[uiIndex] == m_creature->GetEntry())
144  uiIndex = urand(0, MAX_ENTRIES - 1);
145 
146  m_creature->CastSpell(nullptr, 35426, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED); // arcane explosion visual
147  if (m_creature->UpdateEntry(aNetherDrakeEntries[uiIndex]))
148  {
149  // Nihil does only dialogue
150  if (aNetherDrakeEntries[uiIndex] == NPC_NIHIL)
151  {
152  EnterEvadeMode();
153  m_creature->SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_SPAWNING);
154  m_bIsNihil = true;
155  }
156  else
157  AttackStart(pCaster);
158  }
159  }
160  }
161 
162  void UpdateAI(const uint32 uiDiff) override
163  {
164  if (m_bIsNihil)
165  {
166  if (m_uiNihilSpeechTimer < uiDiff)
167  {
168  switch (m_uiNihilSpeechPhase)
169  {
170  case 0:
171  DoScriptText(SAY_NIHIL_1, m_creature);
172  break;
173  case 1:
174  DoScriptText(SAY_NIHIL_2, m_creature);
175  break;
176  case 2:
177  DoScriptText(SAY_NIHIL_3, m_creature);
178  break;
179  case 3:
180  DoScriptText(SAY_NIHIL_4, m_creature);
181  break;
182  case 4:
183  m_creature->SetFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_UNINTERACTIBLE);
184  // take off to location above
185  m_creature->SetLevitate(true);
186  m_creature->SetByteFlag(UNIT_FIELD_BYTES_1, UNIT_BYTES_1_OFFSET_MISC_FLAGS, UNIT_BYTE1_FLAG_FLY_ANIM);
187  m_creature->GetMotionMaster()->MovePoint(1, m_creature->GetPositionX() + 50.0f, m_creature->GetPositionY(), m_creature->GetPositionZ() + 50.0f);
188  break;
189  }
190  ++m_uiNihilSpeechPhase;
191  m_uiNihilSpeechTimer = 5000;
192  }
193  else
194  m_uiNihilSpeechTimer -= uiDiff;
195 
196  // anything below here is not interesting for Nihil, so skip it
197  return;
198  }
199 
200  if (!m_creature->SelectHostileTarget() || !m_creature->GetVictim())
201  return;
202 
203  if (m_uiIntangiblePresenceTimer < uiDiff)
204  {
205  if (DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_INTANGIBLE_PRESENCE) == CAST_OK)
206  m_uiIntangiblePresenceTimer = urand(15000, 30000);
207  }
208  else
209  m_uiIntangiblePresenceTimer -= uiDiff;
210 
211  if (m_uiManaBurnTimer < uiDiff)
212  {
213  if (Unit* pTarget = m_creature->SelectAttackingTarget(ATTACKING_TARGET_RANDOM, 0, SPELL_MANA_BURN, (SELECT_FLAG_PLAYER | SELECT_FLAG_POWER_MANA)))
214  {
215  if (DoCastSpellIfCan(pTarget, SPELL_MANA_BURN) == CAST_OK)
216  m_uiManaBurnTimer = urand(8000, 16000);
217  }
218  }
219  else
220  m_uiManaBurnTimer -= uiDiff;
221 
222  if (m_uiArcaneBlastTimer < uiDiff)
223  {
224  if (DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature->GetVictim(), SPELL_ARCANE_BLAST) == CAST_OK)
225  m_uiArcaneBlastTimer = urand(2500, 7500);
226  }
227  else
228  m_uiArcaneBlastTimer -= uiDiff;
229 
230  DoMeleeAttackIfReady();
231  }
232 };

293 static const uint32 aOgreEntries[] = {19995, 19998, 20334, 20723, 20726, 20730, 20731, 20732, 21296};
294 
295 struct npc_bloodmaul_stout_triggerAI : public ScriptedAI
296 {
297  npc_bloodmaul_stout_triggerAI(Creature* pCreature) : ScriptedAI(pCreature) { Reset(); }
298 
299  uint32 m_uiStartTimer;
300  bool m_bHasValidOgre;
301 
302  ObjectGuid m_selectedOgreGuid;
303 
304  void Reset() override
305  {
306  m_uiStartTimer = 1000;
307  m_bHasValidOgre = false;
308  }
309 
310  void MoveInLineOfSight(Unit* pWho) override
311  {
312  if (m_bHasValidOgre && pWho->GetObjectGuid() == m_selectedOgreGuid && m_creature->IsWithinDistInMap(pWho, 3.5f))
313  {
314  // Handle interaction and run home with EAI
315  m_creature->AI()->SendAIEvent(AI_EVENT_CUSTOM_EVENTAI_A, m_creature, (Creature*)pWho);
316 
317  // Give kill credit to the summoner player
318  if (m_creature->IsTemporarySummon())
319  {
320  if (Player* pSummoner = m_creature->GetMap()->GetPlayer(m_creature->GetSpawnerGuid()))
321  pSummoner->KilledMonsterCredit(m_creature->GetEntry(), m_creature->GetObjectGuid());
322  }
323 
324  if (GameObject* tankard = GetClosestGameObjectWithEntry(m_creature, GO_TANKARD, 2.0f))
325  {
326  tankard->AddObjectToRemoveList();
327  m_creature->ForcedDespawn(2000);
328  }
329 
330  m_bHasValidOgre = false;
331  }
332  }
333 
334  void UpdateAI(const uint32 uiDiff) override
335  {
336  if (m_uiStartTimer)
337  {
338  if (m_uiStartTimer <= uiDiff)
339  {
340  // get all the ogres in range
341  CreatureList lOgreList;
342  for (unsigned int aOgreEntrie : aOgreEntries)
343  GetCreatureListWithEntryInGrid(lOgreList, m_creature, aOgreEntrie, 30.0f);
344 
345  if (lOgreList.empty())
346  {
347  m_uiStartTimer = 5000;
348  return;
349  }
350 
351  // sort by distance and get only the closest
352  lOgreList.sort(ObjectDistanceOrder(m_creature));
353 
354  CreatureList::const_iterator ogreItr = lOgreList.begin();
355  Creature* pOgre = nullptr;
356 
357  do
358  {
359  if ((*ogreItr)->IsAlive() && !(*ogreItr)->HasAura(SPELL_INTOXICATION))
360  pOgre = *ogreItr;
361 
362  ++ogreItr;
363  }
364  while (!pOgre && ogreItr != lOgreList.end());
365 
366  if (!pOgre)
367  {
368  m_uiStartTimer = 5000;
369  return;
370  }
371 
372  // Move ogre to the point
373  float fX, fY, fZ;
374  pOgre->GetMotionMaster()->MoveIdle();
375  pOgre->SetWalk(false, true);
376  m_creature->GetContactPoint(pOgre, fX, fY, fZ);
377  pOgre->GetMotionMaster()->MovePoint(0, fX, fY, fZ);
378 
379  switch (urand(0, 2))
380  {
381  case 0: DoScriptText(SAY_BREW_1, pOgre); break;
382  case 1: DoScriptText(SAY_BREW_2, pOgre); break;
383  case 2: DoScriptText(SAY_BREW_3, pOgre); break;
384  }
385 
386  m_selectedOgreGuid = pOgre->GetObjectGuid();
387  m_uiStartTimer = 0;
388  m_bHasValidOgre = true;
389  }
390  else
391  m_uiStartTimer -= uiDiff;
392  }
393  }
394 };

560  // Prepare levels
561  void DoPrepareLevel()
562  {
563  // this visual is cast only after the first level
564  if (m_uiLevelCount)
565  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_VISUAL_GAME_START, CAST_TRIGGERED);
566  // this part is done only on the first tick
567  else
568  {
569  // lock apexis
570  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_SWITCHED_ON, CAST_TRIGGERED);
571  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_PRE_EVENT_TIMER, CAST_TRIGGERED | CAST_AURA_NOT_PRESENT);
572  }
573 
574  // prepare the buttons and summon the visual auras
575  DoCastSpellIfCan(nullptr, m_bIsLargeEvent ? SPELL_PRE_GAME_BLUE_LARGE : SPELL_PRE_GAME_BLUE_AURA, CAST_TRIGGERED);
576  DoCastSpellIfCan(nullptr, m_bIsLargeEvent ? SPELL_PRE_GAME_GREEN_LARGE : SPELL_PRE_GAME_GREEN_AURA, CAST_TRIGGERED);
577  DoCastSpellIfCan(nullptr, m_bIsLargeEvent ? SPELL_PRE_GAME_RED_LARGE : SPELL_PRE_GAME_RED_AURA, CAST_TRIGGERED);
578  DoCastSpellIfCan(nullptr, m_bIsLargeEvent ? SPELL_PRE_GAME_YELLOW_LARGE : SPELL_PRE_GAME_YELLOW_AURA, CAST_TRIGGERED);

606  {
607  // lock the buttons
608  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_GAME_END_RED, CAST_TRIGGERED);
609  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_GAME_END_BLUE, CAST_TRIGGERED);
610  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_GAME_END_GREEN, CAST_TRIGGERED);
611  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_GAME_END_YELLOW, CAST_TRIGGERED);
612 
613  if (m_bIsLargeEvent)
614  {
615  if (m_uiLevelCount == SIMON_BIG_LEVEL_SUMMON)
616  {
617  BuffPlayers(SPELL_APEXIS_VIBRATIONS);
618  if (Player* player = m_creature->GetMap()->GetPlayer(m_masterPlayerGuid))
619  player->CastSpell(player, SPELL_SIMON_GROUP_REWARD, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
620  DoCompleteGame();
621  }
622  }
623  else
624  {
625  // Complete game if all the levels
626  switch (m_uiLevelCount)
627  {
628  case SIMON_LEVEL_VIBRATIONS:
629  BuffPlayers(SPELL_APEXIS_VIBRATIONS);
630  break;
631  case SIMON_LEVEL_EMANATIONS:
632  BuffPlayers(SPELL_APEXIS_EMANATIONS);
633  break;
634  case SIMON_LEVEL_ENLIGHTENMENT:
635  BuffPlayers(SPELL_APEXIS_ENLIGHTENMENT);
636  DoCompleteGame();
637  break;
638  default: break;
639  }
640  }
641  }
642 
643  void BuffPlayers(uint32 buffId)
644  {
645  if (m_bIsLargeEvent)
646  {
647  if (Player* pPlayer = m_creature->GetMap()->GetPlayer(m_masterPlayerGuid))
648  {
649  if (Group* pGroup = pPlayer->GetGroup())
650  {
651  for (GroupReference* pRef = pGroup->GetFirstMember(); pRef != nullptr; pRef = pRef->next())
652  {
653  if (Player* pMember = pRef->getSource())
654  {
655  // distance check - they need to be close to the Apexis
656  if (!pMember->IsWithinDistInMap(m_creature, 20.0f))
657  continue;
658 
659  DoCastSpellIfCan(pMember, buffId, CAST_TRIGGERED);
660  }
661  }
662  }
663  else
664  DoCastSpellIfCan(pPlayer, buffId, CAST_TRIGGERED);
665  }
666  }
667  else
668  {
669  if (Player* pPlayer = m_creature->GetMap()->GetPlayer(m_masterPlayerGuid))
670  DoCastSpellIfCan(pPlayer, buffId, CAST_TRIGGERED);
671  }
672  }
673 
674  // Complete event - called when the game has been completed succesfully
675  void DoCompleteGame()
676  {
677  // cleanup event after quest is finished
678  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_SWITCHED_OFF, CAST_TRIGGERED);
679  DoPlaySoundToSet(m_creature, SOUND_ID_DISABLE_NODE);
680  Reset();
681  }
682 
683  // Cleanup event - called when event fails
684  void DoCleanupGame()
685  {
686  if (m_bIsLargeEvent)
687  if (Player* player = m_creature->GetMap()->GetPlayer(m_masterPlayerGuid))
688  player->CastSpell(player, SPELL_SIMON_GROUP_REWARD, TRIGGERED_OLD_TRIGGERED);
689 
690  // lock the buttons
691  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_GAME_END_RED, CAST_TRIGGERED);
692  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_GAME_END_BLUE, CAST_TRIGGERED);
693  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_GAME_END_GREEN, CAST_TRIGGERED);
694  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_GAME_END_YELLOW, CAST_TRIGGERED);
695 
696  // unlock apexis and despawn
697  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_SWITCHED_OFF, CAST_TRIGGERED);
698  DoPlaySoundToSet(m_creature, SOUND_ID_DISABLE_NODE);
699  Reset();
700  }
701 
702  void ReceiveAIEvent(AIEventType eventType, Unit* /*pSender*/, Unit* pInvoker, uint32 uiMiscValue) override
703  {
704  switch (m_uiGamePhase)
705  {
706  case PHASE_INACTIVE:
707  if (eventType == AI_EVENT_CUSTOM_A && !m_bIsEventStarted)
708  {
709  m_uiGamePhase = PHASE_LEVEL_PREPARE;
710  m_masterPlayerGuid = pInvoker->GetObjectGuid();
711  m_uiLevelCount = 0;
712  DoPrepareLevel();
713  m_bIsEventStarted = true;
714  break;
715  }
716  case PHASE_LEVEL_PREPARE:
717  // delay before each level - handled by big timer aura
718  if (eventType == AI_EVENT_CUSTOM_A)
719  m_uiGamePhase = PHASE_AI_GAME;
720  break;
721  case PHASE_AI_GAME:
722  // AI game - handled by small timer aura
723  if (eventType == AI_EVENT_CUSTOM_B)
724  {
725  // Move to next phase if the level is setup
726  if (m_uiLevelStage == m_uiLevelCount)
727  {
728  m_uiGamePhase = PHASE_PLAYER_PREPARE;
729  m_uiLevelStage = 0;
730  return;
731  }
732 
733  DoSetupLevel();
734  ++m_uiLevelStage;
735  }
736  break;
737  case PHASE_PLAYER_PREPARE:
738  // Player prepare - handled by small timer aura
739  if (eventType == AI_EVENT_CUSTOM_B)
740  {
741  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_VISUAL_LEVEL_START, CAST_TRIGGERED);
742  DoSetupPlayerLevel();
743 
744  m_uiGamePhase = PHASE_PLAYER_GAME;
745  m_uiPlayerStage = 0;
746  }
747  break;
748  case PHASE_PLAYER_GAME:
749  // Player game - listen to the player moves
750  if (eventType == AI_EVENT_CUSTOM_C)
751  {
752  // good button pressed
753  m_uiPlayerStage = 0;
754  if (uiMiscValue == aApexisGameData[m_vColors[m_uiLevelStage]].m_uiIntrospection)
755  {
756  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_GOOD_PRESS, CAST_TRIGGERED);
757  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, aApexisGameData[m_vColors[m_uiLevelStage]].m_uiVisual, CAST_TRIGGERED);
758 
759  DoPlaySoundToSet(m_creature, aApexisGameData[m_vColors[m_uiLevelStage]].m_uiSoundId);
760 
761  // increase the level stage and reset the event counter
762  ++m_uiLevelStage;
763 
764  // if all buttons were pressed succesfully, then move to next level
765  if (m_uiLevelStage == m_vColors.size())
766  {
767  DoCompleteLevel();
768 
769  m_uiLevelStage = 0;
770  m_uiGamePhase = PHASE_LEVEL_FINISHED;
771  }
772  // cast tick sound
773  else
774  DoCastSpellIfCan(pInvoker, m_bIsLargeEvent ? SPELL_VISUAL_GAME_TICK_LARGE : SPELL_VISUAL_GAME_TICK, CAST_TRIGGERED);
775  }
776  // bad button pressed
777  else
778  {
779  DoCastSpellIfCan(pInvoker, SPELL_BAD_PRESS, CAST_TRIGGERED);
780  if (!m_bIsLargeEvent && !pInvoker->IsAlive()) // if player got killed on small event
781  {
782  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_VISUAL_GAME_FAILED, CAST_TRIGGERED);
783  DoCleanupGame();
784  }
785  }
786  }
787  // AI ticks which handle the player timeout
788  else if (eventType == AI_EVENT_CUSTOM_B)
789  {
790  // if it takes too much time, the event will fail
791  if (m_uiPlayerStage == MAX_SIMON_FAIL_TIMER)
792  {
793  DoCastSpellIfCan(m_creature, SPELL_VISUAL_GAME_FAILED, CAST_TRIGGERED);
794  DoCleanupGame();
795  return;
796  }
797 
798  // Not sure if this is right, but we need to keep the buttons unlocked on every tick
799  DoSetupPlayerLevel();
800  ++m_uiPlayerStage;
801  }
802  break;
803  case PHASE_LEVEL_FINISHED:
804  // small delay until the next level
805  if (eventType == AI_EVENT_CUSTOM_A)
806  {
807  DoPrepareLevel();
808  m_uiGamePhase = PHASE_LEVEL_PREPARE;
809  }
810  break;
811  }
812  }

816

818  {
819 
820  }

2596  void UpdateAI(const uint32 uiDiff) override
2597  {
2598  if (m_timer)
2599  {
2600  if (m_timer <= uiDiff)
2601  {
2602  switch (m_phase)
2603  {
2604  case PHASE_KNEEL_TO_PLAYER:
2605  {
2606  m_randomStuffTimer = 0;
2607  m_creature->SetStandState(UNIT_STAND_STATE_KNEEL);
2608 
2609  m_phase = PHASE_UNKNEEL_TO_PLAYER;
2610  m_timer = 15000;
2611  break;
2612  }
2613  case PHASE_UNKNEEL_TO_PLAYER:
2614  {
2615  m_creature->SetStandState(UNIT_STAND_STATE_STAND);
2616 
2617  m_phase = PHASE_TURN_TO_OGRE;
2618  m_timer = 1200;
2619  m_randomStuffTimer = 5000;
2620 
2621  break;
2622  }
2623  case PHASE_TURN_TO_OGRE:
2624  {
2625  m_creature->HandleEmoteState(EMOTE_STATE_NONE); // Stop dancing
2626 
2627  // turn to random ogre
2628  if (m_supplicants.size() > 1) // safeguard
2629  {
2630  uint32 random = urand(0, m_supplicants.size() - 1);
2631  if (random == m_last)
2632  m_last = (m_last + 1) % (m_supplicants.size() - 1);
2633  if (Creature* supplicant = m_creature->GetMap()->GetCreature(m_supplicants[random]))
2634  m_creature->SetFacingToObject(supplicant);
2635  m_last = random;
2636  }
2637  else if (m_supplicants.size() == 1 && m_last == -1) // only need to do this once
2638  {
2639  if (Creature* supplicant = m_creature->GetMap()->GetCreature(m_supplicants[0]))
2640  m_creature->SetFacingToObject(supplicant);
2641  m_last = 0;
2642  }
2643 
2644  m_timer = urand(3600, 45000);
2645  break;
2646  }
2647  case PHASE_DRUMMER:
2648  {
2649  if (Creature* drumBunny = GetClosestCreatureWithEntry(m_creature, NPC_OGRE_DRUM_BUNNY, 10))
2650  {
2651  m_creature->SetFacingToObject(drumBunny);
2652  m_creature->HandleEmote(EMOTE_ONESHOT_CUSTOMSPELL01);
2653  }
2654 
2655  m_timer = urand(3600, 7300);
2656  break;
2657  }
2658  }
2659  }
2660  else
2661  m_timer -= uiDiff;
2662 
2663  if (m_randomStuffTimer)
2664  {
2665  if (m_randomStuffTimer <= uiDiff)
2666  {
2667  ResetOgreState(false);
2668 
2669  // Do random stuff
2670  switch (urand(0, 4))
2671  {
2672  case 0:
2673  m_creature->HandleEmoteState(EMOTE_STATE_DANCE);
2674  break;
2675  case 1:
2676  m_creature->SetVirtualItem(VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_0, MUG_EQUIP);

2683  m_creature->PlayDistanceSound(ROAR_SOUND);
2684  break;
2685  case 3:
2686  m_creature->HandleEmote(EMOTE_ONESHOT_CHEER);
2687  if (urand(0, 100) <= 20)
2688  m_creature->PlayDistanceSound(CHEER_SOUND);

2695  break;

2700  else

2702  }

2729  break;
